-- South African Coal Prices Have First Weekly Increase in a Month
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-03-26T09:20:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/south-african-coal-prices-have-first-weekly-increase-in-a-month.html
Coal export prices at  South
Africa ’s  Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for
shipping the fuel, increased for the first week in a month,
ending the longest falling streak since November.  Prices (CLSPSARB)  gained 15 cents, or 0.2 percent, to $103.20 a metric
ton in the week ended March 23, the first increase since Feb.
24, according to IHS McCloskey data on Bloomberg. The price is
quoted on a free-on-board basis, which excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  